                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 31, 1973</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Poet-Friend:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We are pleased to inform you that the Second World Congress of Poets will be held November 11-17, 1973 in Taipei, Taiwan, Republic of China. The Congress will be hosted by Chinese Poets Association with the co-sponsorship of United Poets Laureate International, World Poetry Society Intercontinental, Board of Editors of the International Who's Who in Poetry, World Poets' Resource Center, Inc. and its affiliate Eastern Centre of The Poetry Society of England.</p>
                
                <p>We cordially request the honor of your presence at the forthcoming Congress. As you are aware, the Republic China is now the only repository of Chinese culture, and Chinese people are well-known for their warm hospitality. Undoubtedly, you will enjoy your trip to this beautiful island of peace and freedom to get together with your old and new poet-friends from all parts of the world.</p>
                
                <p>Enclosed please find our Invitation with a registration form. Your prompt reply will be greatly appreciated. We look forward to welcoming you with open arms.</p> 
                
                <p>With personal regards and best wishes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Tin-Wen Chung</signed>
                    <signed>Tin-wen Chung
                    Representative of Sponsor</signed> 
                
                    <signed>Amado M. Yuzon</signed>
                    <signed>Amado M. Yuzon
                    Representative of 
                    Co-Sponsors</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MOTTO &amp; THEME:</hi> <hi rend="italics">"World Brotherhood and Peace Through Poetry"</hi> 
                </fw>
                
